&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FP&amp;amp;A Analyst&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Atari&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;East Coast (Remote)&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reports to: Director of FP&amp;amp;A&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Atari, one of the world&#39;s most iconic entertainment brands, is a pioneer in interactive entertainment. With operations spanning gaming, e-commerce, licensing, and hardware, Atari thrives at the intersection of innovation and legacy. Join our dynamic team and play a key role in shaping the financial health of our diverse business operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The FP&amp;amp;A Analyst will support financial planning and analysis across Atari&#39;s business units, including games, e-commerce, licensing, and hardware. Reporting to the Director of FP&amp;amp;A, this individual will contribute to budgeting, forecasting, and financial reporting in a fast-moving environment where not all systems are fully built out yet. This is a growth role and ideal for someone who blends genuine passion for games with solid financial chops and wants to grow alongside the business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the annual budgeting and forecasting process, with hands-on ownership of spreadsheet models and financial data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare regular financial reports and variance analyses across business units&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with and help coordinate the India-based FP&amp;amp;A team on day-to-day deliverables and reporting workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain financial models to support business decisions, M&amp;amp;A activity, and scenario planning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the development of KPI dashboards and data reporting tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work cross-functionally with department heads to gather inputs and provide financial insights&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help identify and implement process improvements as systems and infrastructure continue to evolve&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Experience&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3–5 years of experience in finance; FP&amp;amp;A, corporate reporting, or a mix of both welcome&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in the video game industry (studio, publisher, or platform) strongly preferred. A plus if you understand how games are made, distributed, and monetized&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to multi-entity or global organizations a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced Excel skills. Spreadsheets are central to this role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort working in environments where not everything is systematized yet; a builder mindset&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with AI tools and enthusiasm for applying them to financial workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Power Query or similar dataset tools is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical skills with an ability to communicate financial concepts clearly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Education&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Finance, Accounting, or a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Target Salary:&lt;/strong&gt; $80,000 - $95,000&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us: &lt;/strong&gt;Founded in 1972, Atari is one of the world’s most iconic consumer brands and a pioneer in the video game industry, recognized worldwide for its multi-platform games and licensed products. Atari owns and/or manages a portfolio of more than 400 games and franchises, including globally recognized brands such as Asteroids®, Centipede®, Missile Command®, Pong®, and RollerCoaster Tycoon®.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
