&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;PR &amp;amp; Partnerships Working Student&lt;/strong&gt;, you’ll support Atari’s local and European PR and partnership efforts in a fixed-term, part-time role of around 5–10 hours per week, with the possibility to extend the contract. You’ll help with media outreach, announcement coordination, partner research, interview coordination, and communication around our games, products, and regional activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll work closely with the &lt;strong&gt;President Europe&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Senior Director, Marcoms&lt;/strong&gt;, while collaborating with internal teams across marketing, communications, publishing, partnerships, and product where needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support local and countrywide PR outreach across Germany and Europe, helping us build and maintain strong relationships with press, media contacts, creators, and relevant industry stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft, coordinate, and publish announcements across LinkedIn and other relevant social platforms, including company updates, product news, partnership announcements, and press-facing communication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help distribute announcements externally to journalists, media outlets, partners, and relevant communities to increase visibility and interest around Atari Europe, Atari’s wider company activities, and selected product initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and reach out to potential partners, PR partners, media partners, cultural institutions, gaming communities, and other relevant collaboration opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate PR-related activities such as interviews, press briefings, media requests, follow-ups, scheduling, and internal alignment between teams and external stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and support media coverage around Atari games, products, platforms, and selected initiatives, including areas such as MobyGames, publishing activities, and potentially hardware-related projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help prepare press materials, short briefings, outreach lists, communication summaries, and partner research to support ongoing PR and business development efforts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Atari’s President Europe and Senior Director of Sales &amp;amp; Marketing to support high-impact communication around Atari’s games, products, partnerships, and regional growth across Europe.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
